  "relevant_summary": "The survival and growth of canopy algae transplanted onto subtidal artificial structures are influenced by several key factors. Wave-exposure and surrounding habitat significantly affect survival, with some studies reporting complete transplant failure regardless of protective measures. The presence of cages around transplants is crucial - caged transplants show increased cover and survival compared to uncaged ones, though the mesh size of cages does not always significantly impact growth. Surface orientation has mixed effects, influencing growth in some studies but not affecting survival in others. Protective caging consistently enhances both canopy algae cover and survival on subtidal artificial structures.",
